Strauss-Kahn Announces Choice for IMF Deputy Managing Director

-- B y   T i m o t h y   R .   H o m a n
-- 
2011-02-23T22:53:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/strauss-kahn-announces-choice-for-imf-deputy-managing-director.html
Dominique Strauss-Kahn, head of the  International Monetary Fund , today announced his choice for
deputy managing director at the Washington-based lender.  Nemat Shafik, 48, will succeed Murilo Portugalpending
approval by the  IMF  executive board, the fund said today in an
e-mail statement.  Portugal  is scheduled to step down on March 4,
according to the IMF, and has been named head of  Brazil ’s
Banking Federation.  “A global citizen with a global reputation in fields
ranging from emerging markets, international development, the
Middle East and Africa, to the financial sector, Ms. Shafik
brings to the Fund extensive experience in policy-making,
management and academia,” Strauss-Kahn said in the statement.  Shafik is a national of Egypt, the U.K. and U.S., according
to the IMF. She has served as the permanent secretary of the
U.K.  Department for International Development  since March 2008.
She was also a vice president of the  World Bank , where she was
responsible for a private sector and infrastructure portfolio of
investments, according to the IMF statement.  Shafik is a graduate of the University of Massachusetts-
Amherst in the U.S. and the London School of Economics. She has
a doctorate of economics from Oxford University, the IMF
statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Timothy R. Homan in Washington at 
